1
00:00:21,647 --> 00:00:22,940
<i>Teo, pull over and get out.</i>
<i>I'll drive myself.</i>

2
00:00:23,023 --> 00:00:23,983
<i>Just go home and come back tomorrow.</i>

3
00:00:24,066 --> 00:00:25,025
- Ma! Ma!
- Jenny!

4
00:00:25,109 --> 00:00:26,485
Teo, they took my daughter!

5
00:00:26,569 --> 00:00:28,320
<i>If you want to see your daughter alive,</i>

6
00:00:28,404 --> 00:00:29,405
<i>then come find her!</i>

7
00:00:29,488 --> 00:00:31,991
Move them to the compound
in Palacios. Do it now!

8
00:00:32,074 --> 00:00:33,200
-<i> I'm sorry about this, Jepoy.</i>
- It's okay.

9
00:00:33,284 --> 00:00:35,661
<i>She was kidnapped,</i>
<i>and her mom died in front of her.</i>

10
00:00:35,745 --> 00:00:37,288
<i>I can't let her travel alone.</i>

11
00:00:37,371 --> 00:00:39,540
The Veronas are murderers. They're demons.

12
00:00:39,623 --> 00:00:41,834
Think about yourself

13
00:00:41,917 --> 00:00:43,711
<i>and don't waste what I did for you.</i>

14
00:00:43,794 --> 00:00:47,089
<i>You think I'd still be here</i>
<i>if I just let them have their way with me?</i>

15
00:00:47,173 --> 00:00:49,675
Next time you put me in danger...

16
00:00:49,759 --> 00:00:51,552
You don't know what I'm capable of.

17
00:00:51,635 --> 00:00:52,470
<i>We're going on a vacation.</i>

18
00:00:52,553 --> 00:00:53,387
You remember that resort...

19
00:00:53,471 --> 00:00:54,346
...you wanted to go to?

20
00:00:54,430 --> 00:00:55,931
<i>We can check it out</i>
<i>and stay there for a few days.</i>

21
00:00:56,015 --> 00:00:57,850
Teo!

22
00:01:02,438 --> 00:01:05,900
♪ <i>Love is never gone... ♪</i>

23
00:01:51,570 --> 00:01:54,698


24
00:01:54,782 --> 00:01:56,200
Open the door!

25
00:01:57,451 --> 00:01:59,787


26
00:01:59,870 --> 00:02:01,747


27
00:02:01,831 --> 00:02:03,165
Ace!

28
00:02:03,916 --> 00:02:05,584
Let me out of here!

29
00:02:11,841 --> 00:02:13,467
Have you gotten ahold of Ace?

30
00:02:13,551 --> 00:02:14,677
Not yet.

31
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:16,470
- How about Gem?
I haven't heard from her either.

32
00:02:16,554 --> 00:02:18,305
Did Ace or Gem say...

33
00:02:18,389 --> 00:02:20,766
...that they wouldn't be
joining us for dinner tonight?

34
00:02:20,850 --> 00:02:21,934
No.

35
00:02:22,017 --> 00:02:23,352
-

36
00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:26,438

Eric, have you contacted Ace?

37
00:02:29,567 --> 00:02:32,194
Okay. Keep us updated.

38
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:34,113
What did he say?

39
00:02:34,196 --> 00:02:35,406
Papa.

40
00:02:36,615 --> 00:02:38,200
Where's Teo?

41
00:02:39,577 --> 00:02:41,328
He was the one who picked them up, right?

42
00:02:42,538 --> 00:02:43,372
Steven.

43
00:02:43,455 --> 00:02:45,374
I've already spoken to Mr. Alonzo, Judge.

44
00:02:45,457 --> 00:02:47,293
Teo isn't answering his calls either.

45
00:02:53,841 --> 00:02:55,843


46
00:02:55,926 --> 00:02:57,136
Sir.

47
00:03:01,307 --> 00:03:02,474
Sir.

48
00:03:02,558 --> 00:03:05,477


49
00:03:05,561 --> 00:03:06,937
-
Hello?

50
00:03:07,021 --> 00:03:08,480
Who are you?

51
00:03:08,564 --> 00:03:09,815
Where's Teo?

52
00:03:09,899 --> 00:03:11,483
Ma'am, I work as a rider.

53
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:14,570
I just happened to pass by
and saw someone.

54
00:03:14,653 --> 00:03:17,865
Uh... ma'am, is this the person
you're looking for?

55
00:03:20,743 --> 00:03:23,954
Oh, my God! Is he dead?

56
00:03:24,038 --> 00:03:25,789
Where's my son?

57
00:03:25,873 --> 00:03:28,417
- Ace?
What happened, Ma?

58
00:03:30,127 --> 00:03:31,587
Where are you?

59
00:03:43,098 --> 00:03:45,851


60
00:03:51,148 --> 00:03:53,108
Hey! Get me out!

61
00:03:53,692 --> 00:03:55,611
Let me go!

62
00:03:57,112 --> 00:03:58,906
Get me out of here!

63
00:04:01,533 --> 00:04:03,619
Get me out, please! Get me out!

64
00:04:03,702 --> 00:04:05,454
-
Anyone there? Get me out!

65
00:04:05,537 --> 00:04:07,247
Please let me out!

66
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:11,293
Stay there, okay?

67
00:04:16,674 --> 00:04:19,218
Papa! Mama!

68
00:04:19,301 --> 00:04:22,096
Help! Help!

69
00:04:23,013 --> 00:04:24,556
Papa!

70
00:04:25,557 --> 00:04:29,228


71
00:04:32,731 --> 00:04:34,817

Our car suddenly stopped.

72
00:04:35,859 --> 00:04:38,195
When I checked the car,

73
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:40,030
I found out something had broken.

74
00:04:40,114 --> 00:04:42,282
When I was going to get the tools,

75
00:04:42,366 --> 00:04:44,952
someone hit me in the head.

76
00:04:45,035 --> 00:04:46,370
Then, I woke up here.

77
00:04:46,453 --> 00:04:48,247
So then, where is my son?

78
00:04:48,330 --> 00:04:50,290
Why did you leave him?

79
00:04:50,374 --> 00:04:51,875

You should have protected him!

80
00:04:51,959 --> 00:04:53,627
Katarina, stop.

81
00:04:53,711 --> 00:04:56,839
Ma'am,
please don't get mad at him.

82
00:04:56,922 --> 00:04:58,882
My son is also a victim.

83
00:04:58,966 --> 00:05:02,761
If the culprit had hit him badly,

84
00:05:02,845 --> 00:05:05,264
his condition might have been worse.

85
00:05:05,848 --> 00:05:07,099
I understand.

86
00:05:09,518 --> 00:05:11,145
Chief, I'll leave it to you.

87
00:05:11,228 --> 00:05:13,981
I trust that you'll find my son
and my daughter-in-law.

88
00:05:14,064 --> 00:05:15,315
Yes, Judge.

89
00:05:18,068 --> 00:05:20,446
Sir, we already saw the scan.

90
00:05:20,529 --> 00:05:23,282
The patient's head injury
isn't that serious.

91
00:05:23,365 --> 00:05:25,075
It's just a mild concussion.

92
00:05:25,159 --> 00:05:28,579
For now, he's under observation
for the next 24 hours.

93
00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:31,165
- Thank you, Doc.
Excuse me.

94
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:45,637
Just keep me posted if there's any leads.

95
00:05:45,721 --> 00:05:48,640
But I hope this won't get out,
especially to the media.

96
00:05:48,724 --> 00:05:49,975
No problem, Judge.

97
00:05:50,059 --> 00:05:51,769
We will bring your son back.

98
00:05:51,852 --> 00:05:53,645

Well, I just hope it's not too late.

99
00:05:53,729 --> 00:05:54,813
Katarina.

100
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:57,441


101
00:05:57,941 --> 00:05:58,984
Ace?

102
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:01,153
Judge Divino Verona.

103
00:06:01,236 --> 00:06:03,072
Put it on speaker mode.

104
00:06:04,323 --> 00:06:05,157


105
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:07,242

We have your son and his wife.

106
00:06:07,326 --> 00:06:08,786
Why should I believe you?

107
00:06:08,869 --> 00:06:09,745


108
00:06:11,789 --> 00:06:14,541
Oh, my God! Ace!

109
00:06:15,334 --> 00:06:16,627
Divino.

110
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:18,837
- What do you want?
<i>Twenty million pesos...</i>

111
00:06:18,921 --> 00:06:21,090
<i>for the lives of your son and his wife.</i>

112
00:06:21,173 --> 00:06:24,051
You don't know
who you're going up against.

113
00:06:24,134 --> 00:06:25,636
<i>Oh, I do.</i>

114
00:06:25,719 --> 00:06:29,306
<i>That's how I know</i>
<i>you have 20 million pesos.</i>

115
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:31,558
<i>I'll call you again</i>
<i>on how you can send the money.</i>

116
00:06:31,642 --> 00:06:32,893
<i>Make sure there are no cops,</i>

117
00:06:32,976 --> 00:06:35,354
<i>or I'll have the heads</i>
<i>of these two chopped off.</i>

118
00:06:35,437 --> 00:06:36,355


119
00:06:39,733 --> 00:06:41,693
I'm so worried, Divino.

120
00:06:44,113 --> 00:06:45,531
Ace is in danger.

121
00:06:48,826 --> 00:06:51,036
We got a copy of the CCTV footage

122
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:54,373
showing the whereabouts of your son's car.

123
00:06:54,456 --> 00:06:57,126
We last tracked them
heading out of Manila,

124
00:06:57,209 --> 00:06:59,795

on the way to San Cupertino Resort.

125
00:06:59,878 --> 00:07:01,505

The area outside of Manila

126
00:07:01,588 --> 00:07:04,299
is unfortunately
a dead zone with no cameras,

127
00:07:04,383 --> 00:07:05,801
so we lost track of them.

128
00:07:07,803 --> 00:07:09,555
Thank you.

129
00:07:09,638 --> 00:07:12,099
We'll let you know
as soon as there are updates.

130
00:07:12,182 --> 00:07:14,268
- All right.
- Thank you.

131
00:07:19,690 --> 00:07:21,692
This is taking too much time!

132
00:07:21,775 --> 00:07:24,403
Why did we have to report it to the cops?

133
00:07:24,486 --> 00:07:26,196
Why don't we just pay the ransom

134
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:28,490
and let our men handle those kidnappers?

135
00:07:28,574 --> 00:07:30,284
No, Katarina.

136
00:07:30,367 --> 00:07:32,244
When this happened to Ace before,

137
00:07:32,327 --> 00:07:33,579
we did not involve the police.

138
00:07:33,662 --> 00:07:35,289
Now, he's scarred for life.

139
00:07:35,372 --> 00:07:36,748
I don't want that to happen again.

140
00:07:36,832 --> 00:07:38,125
So, what are we going to do now?

141
00:07:38,208 --> 00:07:40,043
Just sit and wait for updates?

142
00:07:40,127 --> 00:07:42,129
I'm doing everything I can.

143
00:07:42,212 --> 00:07:44,214
The police are doing their job.

144
00:07:44,798 --> 00:07:49,803
As for you,
all you have to do is stay calm.

145
00:07:50,971 --> 00:07:51,972
You hear me?

146
00:07:59,229 --> 00:08:01,273
You really didn't see anything?

147
00:08:01,356 --> 00:08:04,109
I'm so sorry, Judge.
I really didn't see anything.

148
00:08:05,068 --> 00:08:06,778
I was knocked out.

149
00:08:06,862 --> 00:08:09,948
I didn't see what they looked like
or how many there were.

150
00:08:10,657 --> 00:08:11,658
Judge.

151
00:08:12,784 --> 00:08:15,996
My son has already told the police
everything he knows.

152
00:08:18,290 --> 00:08:19,958
Don't you believe Teo?

153
00:08:20,042 --> 00:08:22,836
I've seen a hundred cases like this.

154
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:24,838
It is usually an inside job.

155
00:08:26,673 --> 00:08:29,051
So, Teo, if you're lying, I'll find out.

156
00:08:29,676 --> 00:08:31,720
That's all there is to it, Judge.

157
00:08:31,803 --> 00:08:33,805
Give your phone to Eric.

158
00:08:33,889 --> 00:08:36,808
I need to check all your texts and calls.

159
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,400
I'm not hiding anything, Judge.

160
00:08:45,484 --> 00:08:47,611
"Pick me up now, Teo.
Get my things first."

161
00:08:48,403 --> 00:08:49,279
"Teo, get the car ready. I need to go."

162
00:08:52,407 --> 00:08:55,869
They're only texts and calls
from Attorney Ace and Ma'am Gem,

163
00:08:55,953 --> 00:08:57,120
and his father.

164
00:08:58,497 --> 00:08:59,539
Who's Issay?

165
00:09:00,415 --> 00:09:02,209
She's my youngest child...

166
00:09:02,292 --> 00:09:03,585
Teo's sister.

167
00:09:04,336 --> 00:09:06,588
Double-check with the telephone company.

168
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:09,758
I don't want any stone left unturned.

169
00:09:09,841 --> 00:09:10,926
Yes, sir.

170
00:09:26,149 --> 00:09:28,360
Make sure
no one enters his room or talks to him

171
00:09:28,443 --> 00:09:29,695
apart from his family.

172
00:09:30,404 --> 00:09:33,573
If you see anyone suspicious,
call me right away.

173
00:09:33,657 --> 00:09:34,741
Yes, Judge.

174
00:09:36,285 --> 00:09:39,079
Son,
why is the judge so suspicious of you?

175
00:09:40,247 --> 00:09:42,874
- You're the one who got hurt.
- I don't know.

176
00:09:43,959 --> 00:09:45,585
Maybe you had something to do with it.

177
00:09:45,669 --> 00:09:47,754
Not you too, Pa.

178
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:49,589
Well...

179
00:09:50,632 --> 00:09:52,050
I'm just making sure.

180
00:09:52,134 --> 00:09:54,177
I understand Judge.

181
00:09:54,261 --> 00:09:55,971
Losing a son is really tough.

182
00:09:57,222 --> 00:09:59,641
You don't know what's happening to him,

183
00:09:59,725 --> 00:10:03,186
if he's having a hard time
or if he's still breathing.

184
00:10:04,354 --> 00:10:06,023
I just want to go home, Pa.

185
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:08,317
You can't be discharged
until the doctor says so.

186
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:10,569
You're still under observation.

187
00:10:11,361 --> 00:10:14,489
Besides, there are guards
outside the room.

188
00:10:15,282 --> 00:10:19,870
Maybe Judge is worried that
the kidnappers would come back for you.

189
00:10:23,874 --> 00:10:25,542
Are there any updates...

190
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:29,046
or at least a lead?

191
00:10:29,629 --> 00:10:30,881
Still nothing?

192
00:10:30,964 --> 00:10:32,674
The kidnappers
planned all of it carefully.

193
00:10:32,758 --> 00:10:34,343
How so?

194
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:39,306
Eric said that Ace and Gem
were going to Batangas that day.

195
00:10:39,389 --> 00:10:40,849
None of us knew about it,

196
00:10:40,932 --> 00:10:43,268
and Ace didn't tell anyone
about that trip.

197
00:10:43,352 --> 00:10:46,646
Yeah, we were even expecting them
at dinner.

198
00:10:46,730 --> 00:10:49,566
The kidnappers knew about Ace's plan

199
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:52,527
and ambushed them
on their way to their destination.

200
00:10:52,611 --> 00:10:54,946
So, what are you--
what are you saying?

201
00:10:55,697 --> 00:10:57,657
That someone is spying on us?

202
00:10:57,741 --> 00:11:01,203
It's either that,
or it's really an inside job.

203
00:11:06,249 --> 00:11:08,085
- Oh, my gosh.
- Ma.

204
00:11:08,877 --> 00:11:11,463
It's okay. Ace will be okay.

205
00:11:30,315 --> 00:11:33,068
Well, Judge?
Do you have the 20 million pesos ready?

206
00:11:33,151 --> 00:11:34,444
Tell me when and where.

207
00:11:34,945 --> 00:11:37,864
I want it by 2:00 a.m.

208
00:11:37,948 --> 00:11:40,200
<i>at the end of Sunset Drive in Bulacan.</i>

209
00:11:40,283 --> 00:11:42,202
<i>Leave the money at the vacant lot.</i>

210
00:11:42,285 --> 00:11:43,370
<i>Make sure you're alone.</i>

211
00:11:43,453 --> 00:11:47,499
If I see you with someone,
I'll kill those two.

212
00:11:53,004 --> 00:11:54,172
We'll do an ocular inspection

213
00:11:54,256 --> 00:11:56,591
so we can find strategic areas.

214
00:11:56,675 --> 00:11:59,219
The kidnapper shouldn't know
that you're with the cops.

215
00:11:59,302 --> 00:12:00,762
I will give a signal,

216
00:12:00,846 --> 00:12:04,766
but please make sure
that Ace and Gem are safe.

217
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:05,934
Yes, Judge.

218
00:12:12,149 --> 00:12:13,150
Take care, Judge.

219
00:12:14,067 --> 00:12:15,402
I'll leave you in charge here.

220
00:12:15,485 --> 00:12:16,862
Yes.

221
00:12:17,612 --> 00:12:18,947
Pa.

222
00:12:19,698 --> 00:12:20,866
Take care.

223
00:12:21,408 --> 00:12:22,784
Thank you, dear.

224
00:12:24,119 --> 00:12:26,705
Divino, please be careful.

225
00:12:27,789 --> 00:12:30,625
- Bring our son home safe.
- I will.

226
00:12:41,970 --> 00:12:44,306
Did you get everything I need?

227
00:12:44,389 --> 00:12:45,849
Yes, it's all there in your bag.

228
00:12:45,932 --> 00:12:48,435
I packed your clothes, shoes,
and the keys to the motorcycle

229
00:12:48,518 --> 00:12:50,979
that you bought from Mr. Chito.

230
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,815
I tested it for impact and gave it a spin,

231
00:12:53,899 --> 00:12:56,234
and it's working great.

232
00:12:56,318 --> 00:12:57,861
That's what I rode here, actually.

233
00:12:57,944 --> 00:12:59,029
Thank you.

234
00:12:59,613 --> 00:13:02,574
You can go now.
You have classes tomorrow, right?

235
00:13:02,657 --> 00:13:04,326
Yes, but that's okay.

236
00:13:04,409 --> 00:13:05,869
I'll just take a make-up test.

237
00:13:05,952 --> 00:13:08,663
Besides, Mr. Alonzo needs some rest.

238
00:13:08,747 --> 00:13:10,665
Oh, you have a test?

239
00:13:10,749 --> 00:13:12,709
You can go home then.
I have guards with me anyway.

240
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:15,295
I bet there are even more
outside the hospital.

241
00:13:15,378 --> 00:13:17,172
Plus, I can take care of myself.

242
00:13:17,255 --> 00:13:18,965
You can go. Don't take the motorcycle.

243
00:13:19,049 --> 00:13:20,842
Just get a ride home. I'll cover the fare.

244
00:13:20,926 --> 00:13:23,428
- Are you sure?
- Yes, you can go.

245
00:13:23,512 --> 00:13:26,681
Okay. I'll just help Mr. Alonzo tomorrow.

246
00:13:26,765 --> 00:13:28,642
- Get well soon.
- Take care.

247
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:35,458
Gem!

248
00:14:36,459 --> 00:14:37,544
Gem!

249
00:14:40,964 --> 00:14:42,007
Gem!

250
00:14:42,090 --> 00:14:44,092
Love! Love!

251
00:14:44,175 --> 00:14:46,011
Love, I'm here!

252
00:14:46,094 --> 00:14:47,012
Love!

253
00:14:47,095 --> 00:14:48,138
Gem!

254
00:14:49,973 --> 00:14:50,890
Love?

255
00:14:50,974 --> 00:14:52,767
Ace, I'm here!

256
00:14:54,019 --> 00:14:54,936
Gem!

257
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:56,730
- Love!
- Where are you?

258
00:14:56,813 --> 00:14:59,190
Love!

259
00:14:59,274 --> 00:15:00,233
Gem!

260
00:15:00,317 --> 00:15:02,319
Please, Ace! I'm here!

261
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:03,570
Gem!

262
00:15:03,653 --> 00:15:05,864
- Please! Open the door, please!
- Love?

263
00:15:05,947 --> 00:15:08,074
Love! I'll get you out! Hold on!

264
00:15:08,158 --> 00:15:09,659
Hurry up!

265
00:15:14,998 --> 00:15:17,500
- Hold on, I'll get you out!
- Open the door, please!

266
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:22,213
Love!

267
00:15:22,297 --> 00:15:23,923
Ace! Let me out!

268
00:15:27,469 --> 00:15:29,387
Ace!

269
00:15:30,472 --> 00:15:33,016
Please! Let me out!

270
00:15:33,099 --> 00:15:35,060
Ace! Help me!

271
00:15:37,437 --> 00:15:39,439
Please, let me out!

272
00:15:53,370 --> 00:15:54,996
- Teo...
- Let's go.

273
00:15:56,623 --> 00:15:58,625
How did you get here?

274
00:16:00,794 --> 00:16:02,212
Was this your doing?

275
00:16:02,295 --> 00:16:06,549
I did this so you could be free
from the Veronas.

276
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:08,426
Don't worry, they won't suspect us.

277
00:16:08,510 --> 00:16:09,886
We planned this carefully.

278
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:11,346
We?

279
00:16:11,846 --> 00:16:13,181
Gimo and I.

280
00:16:13,264 --> 00:16:16,601
I've been friends with Gem
since Morocco.

281
00:16:16,685 --> 00:16:18,603
Do you remember what happened in Morocco?

282
00:16:18,687 --> 00:16:21,189
We were going to escape from Khaled...

283
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:23,274
but then you arrived.

284
00:16:23,358 --> 00:16:25,193
You ruined our plan.

285
00:16:25,777 --> 00:16:28,071
My life was ruined because of that, too.

286
00:16:28,780 --> 00:16:30,448
Is that why you're seeking revenge?

287
00:16:31,074 --> 00:16:32,158
No.

288
00:16:32,742 --> 00:16:34,744
I finally realize
what kind of hell Gem walked into

289
00:16:34,828 --> 00:16:36,579
just to get me out.

290
00:16:36,663 --> 00:16:39,249
Now all I want
is for Gem to be free, too.

291
00:16:40,166 --> 00:16:41,501
I'll help you.

292
00:16:54,013 --> 00:16:55,432
Be careful.

293
00:16:58,143 --> 00:17:01,312
Gimo told me
that you can't escape from the Veronas

294
00:17:02,063 --> 00:17:05,108
because the money
you stole in Morocco is missing.

295
00:17:05,608 --> 00:17:06,985
Teo.

296
00:17:07,068 --> 00:17:08,611
The moment I get the ransom...

297
00:17:09,446 --> 00:17:12,449
it's all yours. Buy your freedom with it.

298
00:17:15,910 --> 00:17:17,829
I'll help you escape, Gem.

299
00:17:20,081 --> 00:17:21,666
It's not that easy.

300
00:17:22,876 --> 00:17:24,461
Why not?

301
00:17:24,544 --> 00:17:27,130
You've done it in Morocco.
You could do it again.

302
00:17:27,213 --> 00:17:29,841
Enough. It's not happening.

303
00:17:32,427 --> 00:17:34,012
Is it because of the money?

304
00:17:34,763 --> 00:17:36,014
Luxury?

305
00:17:37,098 --> 00:17:39,392
- But Gem, even--
- Because I can't leave you.

306
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:57,577
Teo, don't involve yourself in my mess.

307
00:17:59,788 --> 00:18:01,790
I have no regrets.

308
00:18:03,082 --> 00:18:06,461
I didn't tell you my plan
because you wouldn't have agreed.

309
00:18:06,544 --> 00:18:08,213
I definitely wouldn't have agreed.

310
00:18:09,547 --> 00:18:11,299
You'll get in trouble again.

311
00:18:13,343 --> 00:18:15,178
I don't even care
if that happens again...

312
00:18:16,304 --> 00:18:18,097
as long as you're safe.

313
00:18:20,975 --> 00:18:23,770
Once I get the money...

314
00:18:23,853 --> 00:18:25,563
and they've ransomed Ace,

315
00:18:25,647 --> 00:18:27,148
get out of here.

316
00:18:27,774 --> 00:18:28,983
What about you?

317
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:32,153
I'll resign.

318
00:18:32,237 --> 00:18:33,488
I won't come back to--

319
00:18:33,571 --> 00:18:35,198
Teo, it's not that easy.

320
00:18:35,865 --> 00:18:39,160
They won't stop
until they find out the truth.

321
00:18:39,244 --> 00:18:40,954
I'll handle it.

322
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:46,668
Ah! I forgot.

323
00:18:48,253 --> 00:18:50,880
Use this to call me. Just me, okay?

324
00:18:50,964 --> 00:18:52,799
Don't call home.

325
00:18:52,882 --> 00:18:55,009
Don't worry,
there's a camera in the container.

326
00:18:55,093 --> 00:18:56,469
I can keep an eye on you there.

327
00:19:02,684 --> 00:19:04,519
What about Ace?

328
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:06,855
You don't need to know.

329
00:19:06,938 --> 00:19:09,607
So in case something happens,
you really have no idea.

330
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:45,894
Perez, the boss needs me downstairs.

331
00:19:45,977 --> 00:19:48,021
- Watch the door.
- All right.

332
00:21:15,108 --> 00:21:16,275
<i>Teo.</i>

333
00:21:16,359 --> 00:21:18,194
Teo, don't go in there.

334
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:20,154
You're right, they have back-up.

335
00:21:20,238 --> 00:21:22,573
<i>This bastard won't back down.</i>

336
00:21:23,324 --> 00:21:24,409
I know.

337
00:21:24,492 --> 00:21:26,077
I can see them now.

338
00:21:47,932 --> 00:21:49,392
Where are you?

339
00:21:49,475 --> 00:21:51,227
The money is already here.

340
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:53,312
You have people with you, Judge.

341
00:21:53,396 --> 00:21:54,439
I can see them.

342
00:21:54,522 --> 00:21:56,315
<i>I'm not playing around.</i>

343
00:21:56,399 --> 00:21:58,109
Give me my son.

344
00:21:58,192 --> 00:22:00,194
<i>I'm not playing around either.</i>

345
00:22:00,278 --> 00:22:02,655
<i>Which part of your child</i>
<i>do you want me to send to you?</i>

346
00:22:03,197 --> 00:22:04,323
His ear?

347
00:22:04,407 --> 00:22:05,700
His foot?

348
00:22:05,783 --> 00:22:07,410
<i>Or the rest of his fingers?</i>

349
00:22:09,620 --> 00:22:10,997
<i>Hurry up, Judge.</i>

350
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:13,124
You won't like it when I get bored.

351
00:22:13,207 --> 00:22:15,251
If something bad happens to my son,

352
00:22:15,334 --> 00:22:18,212
I'll kill you myself!

353
00:22:33,895 --> 00:22:35,146
Let's go back to the hospital.

354
00:23:19,982 --> 00:23:21,109
Judge.

355
00:23:38,126 --> 00:23:40,044
I wanted to confirm something.

356
00:23:41,796 --> 00:23:44,674
Before the kidnappers hit you in the head,

357
00:23:45,383 --> 00:23:46,509
did you see them?

358
00:23:47,176 --> 00:23:49,095
- What?
- Answer my question.

359
00:23:50,847 --> 00:23:52,598
First of all, Judge,

360
00:23:53,349 --> 00:23:55,184
I don't know how many there were.

361
00:23:55,268 --> 00:23:57,145
You told me there were two.

362
00:23:57,228 --> 00:23:59,272
I never told you how many there were.

363
00:23:59,355 --> 00:24:01,816
They hit me in the head,
and I lost consciousness.

364
00:24:01,899 --> 00:24:04,068
I didn't see their face.

365
00:24:05,611 --> 00:24:08,197
You were on medication
when I talked to you.

366
00:24:09,532 --> 00:24:10,950
How do you remember that?

367
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:14,662
I don't remember what I told you.

368
00:24:14,745 --> 00:24:18,040
All I remember is what happened to me.

369
00:24:18,124 --> 00:24:19,876
That's all it really is.

370
00:24:22,211 --> 00:24:23,296
Teo...

371
00:24:23,796 --> 00:24:25,214
Oh...

372
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:27,300
Judge.

373
00:24:27,383 --> 00:24:28,759
Why are you here?

374
00:24:28,843 --> 00:24:32,763
I just stopped by to see Teo after work.

375
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:35,641
At this time?

376
00:24:35,725 --> 00:24:37,894
It's pretty late, Larajean,

377
00:24:37,977 --> 00:24:39,770
to be visiting...

378
00:24:39,854 --> 00:24:41,272
your coworker.

379
00:24:42,106 --> 00:24:45,067
Well... you see,
actually, Judge...

380
00:24:46,027 --> 00:24:47,278
uh...

381
00:24:50,364 --> 00:24:52,867
Well, there's...

382
00:24:54,285 --> 00:24:57,038
there's... there's something
going on between us.

383
00:24:57,705 --> 00:25:01,167
Oh, you know,
it's private, but not a secret.

384
00:25:01,250 --> 00:25:02,710
We're just lowkey.

385
00:25:03,461 --> 00:25:05,671
What about you, Judge?
What brings you here?

386
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:11,594
Uh, I'm sorry to keep you waiting, baby.

387
00:25:11,677 --> 00:25:14,597
I stopped by to get your favorite food.

388
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:17,642
Did the doctors say that you could eat?

389
00:25:33,783 --> 00:25:35,117
What was that about?

390
00:25:35,201 --> 00:25:38,579
I was protecting you
in case something happens again.

391
00:25:39,205 --> 00:25:42,333
That is, you won't have another part two
with Yana Kassir.

392
00:25:43,125 --> 00:25:44,252
Come on, Larajean.

393
00:25:44,335 --> 00:25:46,754
Just listen to me.
You'll benefit from it, too.

394
00:25:47,588 --> 00:25:49,173
So...

395
00:25:49,257 --> 00:25:51,968
I've decided to keep my mouth shut.

396
00:25:52,051 --> 00:25:54,053
But the truth is, I don't want to.

397
00:25:54,136 --> 00:25:56,013
I couldn't care less
what happens to Ms. Gem.

398
00:25:56,097 --> 00:25:57,431
But...

399
00:25:58,140 --> 00:25:59,850
I'm doing this because of you.

400
00:25:59,934 --> 00:26:03,145
You'll get in trouble if they find out
you have a history with Ms. Morocco.

401
00:26:03,229 --> 00:26:05,147
So play along and act like
there's something between us.

402
00:26:05,231 --> 00:26:06,565
This is my problem.

403
00:26:06,649 --> 00:26:09,193
You're just getting yourself
dragged into this for nothing.

404
00:26:09,819 --> 00:26:13,322
I just hope that if you know something,
you'll keep it to yourself.

405
00:26:13,406 --> 00:26:15,324
But...

406
00:26:16,075 --> 00:26:19,412
they won't dig into
your connection with Gem

407
00:26:19,495 --> 00:26:22,540
if they're convinced
there's something between us.

408
00:26:25,167 --> 00:26:26,168
I know you.

409
00:26:26,252 --> 00:26:28,838
You're doing this to get closer to me.

410
00:26:28,921 --> 00:26:31,090
And it's unfair to you, Larajean.

411
00:26:32,174 --> 00:26:34,427
When did love become fair?

412
00:26:34,510 --> 00:26:36,804
Just think of it as...

413
00:26:37,346 --> 00:26:40,683
me making up
for everything I did back in Morocco.

414
00:26:40,766 --> 00:26:43,477
And besides,
you don't have to worry about me.

415
00:26:44,854 --> 00:26:47,940
If something happens...

416
00:26:48,024 --> 00:26:49,358
just remember
that you have this as an option.

417
00:26:49,942 --> 00:26:52,445
Don't tell me
you'd rather let the Veronas catch you

418
00:26:52,528 --> 00:26:53,946
than have us get back together.

419
00:26:54,989 --> 00:26:57,199
Even if it sounds delusional.

420
00:27:08,002 --> 00:27:10,004
Hey!
Get me out of here, please!

421
00:27:10,838 --> 00:27:12,590
Get me out of here, please!

422
00:27:13,758 --> 00:27:15,634
Please, just let me go!

423
00:27:15,718 --> 00:27:16,719
Come on!

424
00:27:16,802 --> 00:27:18,346
This is bullshit!

425
00:27:19,930 --> 00:27:22,516
- Let me go!
- Didn't we have an agreement?

426
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:23,934
Hey!

427
00:27:24,727 --> 00:27:27,021
Because you broke our agreement,

428
00:27:27,104 --> 00:27:29,398
<i>the ransom just went up.</i>

429
00:27:29,482 --> 00:27:31,233
<i>Twenty million for your son.</i>

430
00:27:31,317 --> 00:27:33,027
Twenty million for his wife.

431
00:27:33,110 --> 00:27:36,906
I won't be controlled by some criminal!

432
00:27:36,989 --> 00:27:38,949
Enough of this bullshit!

433
00:27:39,033 --> 00:27:40,743
Time is running out.

434
00:27:40,826 --> 00:27:42,119
Please, let me go!

435
00:27:42,203 --> 00:27:45,247
The chances of you seeing your son alive
are slipping away.

436
00:27:49,418 --> 00:27:51,587
You're not careful!

437
00:27:52,088 --> 00:27:54,548
Now, instead of my son
being here with me now,

438
00:27:54,632 --> 00:27:56,092
where is he?

439
00:27:56,175 --> 00:27:58,052
He's still in the hands
of that devil incarnate!

440
00:27:58,135 --> 00:27:59,762
Protocol.

441
00:27:59,845 --> 00:28:01,889
And I don't regret involving them.

442
00:28:01,972 --> 00:28:04,350
Great!

443
00:28:04,433 --> 00:28:06,727
And now, they demand 40 million?

444
00:28:06,811 --> 00:28:09,939
Judge. Ma'am.
We strongly advise you...

445
00:28:10,022 --> 00:28:11,857
not to comply with their demands.

446
00:28:11,941 --> 00:28:13,401
It's only money.

447
00:28:14,318 --> 00:28:16,404
I saw Ace's situation with my own eyes.

448
00:28:16,487 --> 00:28:18,155
I'm not going to waste my time.

449
00:28:18,239 --> 00:28:20,866
My son needs to stay alive,
no matter how much I pay!

450
00:28:20,950 --> 00:28:23,411
I love my son too!

451
00:28:23,494 --> 00:28:25,246
More than my life!

452
00:28:26,163 --> 00:28:27,206
So, fine!

453
00:28:27,289 --> 00:28:29,166
Let's hand them 40 million.

454
00:28:29,792 --> 00:28:33,754
But you better make sure
that those criminals suffer too!

455
00:28:34,213 --> 00:28:36,298
I won't let this slide that easily.

456
00:28:36,382 --> 00:28:38,676
We are not losers.

457
00:28:42,179 --> 00:28:43,806
Especially you, Divino.

458
00:28:44,849 --> 00:28:46,809
You've never lost.

459
00:28:46,892 --> 00:28:48,310
Not even once.

460
00:28:50,271 --> 00:28:51,730
So, please...

461
00:28:51,814 --> 00:28:53,149
not this time.

462
00:28:57,445 --> 00:28:58,863
Can I have a word with you?

463
00:29:05,703 --> 00:29:06,912
Steven.

464
00:29:15,546 --> 00:29:16,589
Ma'am?

465
00:29:18,799 --> 00:29:20,050
Call our men.

466
00:29:20,134 --> 00:29:21,469
I need them.

467
00:29:23,262 --> 00:29:26,098
We can't convince the kidnappers
with legal methods.

468
00:29:26,891 --> 00:29:28,976
So if I want my son alive,

469
00:29:29,727 --> 00:29:32,313
following those rules
will not give him a lifeline.

470
00:29:34,398 --> 00:29:36,650
Ma'am,
does Judge know about this?

471
00:29:36,734 --> 00:29:38,110
No.

472
00:29:38,194 --> 00:29:40,404
And that's why I need you

473
00:29:40,488 --> 00:29:42,823
to keep your mouth shut.

474
00:29:44,950 --> 00:29:48,078
Those protocols won't save my son.

475
00:29:48,662 --> 00:29:51,415
I need to handle this myself.

476
00:30:33,290 --> 00:30:34,166
Hey!

477
00:30:53,310 --> 00:30:54,311
That hurt.

478
00:30:54,395 --> 00:30:56,605
Do you know how dangerous that was?

479
00:30:58,190 --> 00:30:59,900
Teo has this all planned.

480
00:30:59,984 --> 00:31:02,152
He's the mastermind, after all.

481
00:31:04,071 --> 00:31:07,241
All I did was use the gimmick
from back in Morocco.

482
00:31:07,866 --> 00:31:10,452
Are you getting nervous now, Chameleon?

483
00:31:11,662 --> 00:31:13,872
I took that mask off ages ago.

484
00:31:14,498 --> 00:31:17,960
You're still Chameleon deep inside.

485
00:31:18,919 --> 00:31:21,589
Why don't you use that
to escape the Veronas?

486
00:31:21,672 --> 00:31:25,759
And leave Teo and his father
with those monsters?

487
00:31:26,969 --> 00:31:28,220
Use your head.

488
00:31:28,304 --> 00:31:30,806
You know
you can defy the boss, right?

489
00:31:32,558 --> 00:31:34,143
Just leave.

490
00:31:34,226 --> 00:31:36,437
It'll look more convincing now.

491
00:31:37,104 --> 00:31:38,939
Just leave without a trace.

492
00:31:39,023 --> 00:31:42,109
Teo is an adult.
He can take care of himself.

493
00:31:42,192 --> 00:31:44,445
So please, enough with the regret.

494
00:31:46,155 --> 00:31:47,406
Regret?

495
00:31:48,115 --> 00:31:51,035
Regret... and more!

496
00:31:51,118 --> 00:31:52,494
Damn that love.

497
00:31:54,705 --> 00:31:55,914
Thank you, Gimo.

498
00:31:57,458 --> 00:31:59,877
You know me, I can't say no to you.

499
00:32:01,545 --> 00:32:03,255
Vitals are stable.

500
00:32:03,339 --> 00:32:05,049
I'll sign your discharge clearance.

501
00:32:05,132 --> 00:32:06,300
Thank you, Doc.

502
00:32:12,097 --> 00:32:13,599
It's all good, Teo.

503
00:32:14,099 --> 00:32:15,934
Judge and Madam got this covered.

504
00:32:17,353 --> 00:32:19,188
We'll be sending you home.

505
00:32:19,772 --> 00:32:20,814
Thank you.

506
00:32:55,933 --> 00:32:58,394
Steven,
can you give us a minute?

507
00:33:12,241 --> 00:33:13,325
What's up?

508
00:33:14,326 --> 00:33:15,744
Is that the package?

509
00:33:15,828 --> 00:33:17,204
Mm. Here.

510
00:33:18,580 --> 00:33:22,084
Sorry about this.
I can't send it by e-mail.

511
00:33:22,167 --> 00:33:25,379
The Gender and Politics professor
wants it handwritten.

512
00:33:25,462 --> 00:33:27,256
Thank you.

513
00:33:27,339 --> 00:33:28,465
Anytime.

514
00:33:28,549 --> 00:33:30,467
- Here.
- What's that?

515
00:33:30,551 --> 00:33:32,594
Your favorite.
Spanish latte.

516
00:33:33,178 --> 00:33:35,681
And...<i> turon.</i>

517
00:33:35,764 --> 00:33:38,267
It's from Issay, Teo's sister.

518
00:33:39,226 --> 00:33:43,313
I'm really glad you came and not Gracie.

519
00:33:44,898 --> 00:33:46,108
Thanks for this.

520
00:33:46,191 --> 00:33:47,609
Dig in.

521
00:33:59,413 --> 00:34:00,289
What's wrong, Raya?

522
00:34:01,665 --> 00:34:02,833
Sorry.

523
00:34:04,793 --> 00:34:06,336
I can't help it.

524
00:34:06,420 --> 00:34:08,589
I feel overwhelmed.

525
00:34:08,672 --> 00:34:10,883
They're accusing my family of so much.

526
00:34:11,592 --> 00:34:15,095
About the illegal recruitment

527
00:34:15,179 --> 00:34:17,097
and trafficking things.

528
00:34:17,181 --> 00:34:21,226
The witness that died,
they blame us for that too.

529
00:34:21,310 --> 00:34:23,604
And all the canceling online.

530
00:34:23,687 --> 00:34:24,980
And now...

531
00:34:25,647 --> 00:34:29,943
Ace and Gem
are still nowhere to be found.

532
00:34:30,569 --> 00:34:33,655
Some people say
it's karma coming for our family.

533
00:34:36,575 --> 00:34:38,702
It's just so mean.

534
00:34:39,870 --> 00:34:42,998
Even my friends think it's all true.

535
00:34:44,875 --> 00:34:45,876
How about you?

536
00:34:48,212 --> 00:34:49,671
Do you believe it?

537
00:34:49,755 --> 00:34:51,423
O-Of course not.

538
00:34:51,507 --> 00:34:53,217
That's why I'm here, right?

539
00:34:53,300 --> 00:34:55,135
That's why I'm still talking to you.

540
00:34:56,386 --> 00:34:59,264
Raya, whatever happens,
I'll be here with you.

541
00:34:59,348 --> 00:35:01,517
You don't know me well yet.

542
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:04,394
You don't know me that well yet.

543
00:35:04,478 --> 00:35:07,147
I know, I know.

544
00:35:08,148 --> 00:35:09,525
I can see it.

545
00:35:10,108 --> 00:35:12,361
You're snobby,

546
00:35:12,861 --> 00:35:14,112
you're dramatic...

547
00:35:15,030 --> 00:35:16,949
but I know you're a good person.

548
00:35:17,032 --> 00:35:19,576
It's unfair for your friends
to just leave you like that.

549
00:35:19,660 --> 00:35:22,246
So, just smile, okay? I'm here for you.

550
00:35:24,248 --> 00:35:26,166
Thank you.

551
00:37:40,300 --> 00:37:41,259
Here, sir.

552
00:37:41,343 --> 00:37:42,886
This is the estimated radius

553
00:37:42,970 --> 00:37:45,222
of the last call
from Sir Ace's cell phone.

554
00:37:45,305 --> 00:37:48,517
The possible holding area
is about two to three kilometers.

555
00:37:48,600 --> 00:37:52,771
Okay. Let's assign some units around here.

556
00:37:52,854 --> 00:37:54,147
No sirens.

557
00:37:54,231 --> 00:37:55,899
No big movements.

558
00:37:55,983 --> 00:37:58,485
I don't want to alert the kidnappers.

559
00:37:58,568 --> 00:38:01,613
We're evaluating
all extraction options, Judge.

560
00:38:01,697 --> 00:38:03,824
If we need to use force,
we will not hesitate--

561
00:38:03,907 --> 00:38:06,493
No, no, no.
Let's not resort to violence.

562
00:38:06,576 --> 00:38:09,663
Our priority is Ace and Gem.

563
00:38:09,746 --> 00:38:12,958
Ensure their safety above everything.

564
00:38:13,041 --> 00:38:15,961
Your priority will be my son, Ace.

565
00:38:16,044 --> 00:38:18,797
We'll get him out of that place,
and once you have secured him,

566
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:20,924
you have to leave the place immediately.

567
00:38:21,008 --> 00:38:23,427
Now, if you find someone who resists...

568
00:38:24,011 --> 00:38:24,886
end it.

569
00:38:24,970 --> 00:38:26,763
Ma'am, how about Ma'am Gem?

570
00:38:28,306 --> 00:38:29,683
Let me repeat.

571
00:38:30,308 --> 00:38:34,855
Your priority is my son, Ace.

572
00:38:35,397 --> 00:38:38,984
You will get him out of that place,
no matter what.

573
00:38:40,027 --> 00:38:43,905
And I don't care whoever gets left behind.

574
00:38:45,157 --> 00:38:46,074
Is that clear?

575
00:38:55,500 --> 00:38:57,335
Is the 40 million ready?

576
00:38:58,003 --> 00:38:59,421
<i>Where's my son?</i>

577
00:39:01,757 --> 00:39:03,717
He's still alive.

578
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:05,177
He's waiting for...

579
00:39:05,260 --> 00:39:07,137
The 40 million's ready.

580
00:39:07,220 --> 00:39:08,513
<i>I've sent you the location.</i>

581
00:39:08,597 --> 00:39:10,640
Stop playing safe, Judge.

582
00:39:10,724 --> 00:39:12,225
No chaperones.

583
00:39:14,186 --> 00:39:15,520
Got it.

584
00:39:16,646 --> 00:39:17,856
Did you trace the call?

585
00:39:17,939 --> 00:39:19,357
A minute, sir.

586
00:39:27,324 --> 00:39:29,242
Why are you doing this?

587
00:39:33,246 --> 00:39:34,581
To pay you back.

588
00:39:34,664 --> 00:39:37,084
I don't like being in debt,
especially to you.

589
00:39:37,167 --> 00:39:40,545
You've paid so much to set me free.

590
00:39:40,629 --> 00:39:42,714
Your identity

591
00:39:42,798 --> 00:39:44,049
and your entire life.

592
00:39:45,008 --> 00:39:46,802
I want to set you free, too.

593
00:39:46,885 --> 00:39:48,261
I said...

594
00:39:48,845 --> 00:39:51,014
why are you doing this?

595
00:39:51,723 --> 00:39:55,227
Our lives have been intertwined
for a long time.

596
00:39:55,811 --> 00:39:57,270
Mm...

597
00:39:57,354 --> 00:40:01,525
So, you're doing this
so we can be rid of each other?

598
00:40:01,608 --> 00:40:04,236
I don't ever regret meeting you.

599
00:40:06,321 --> 00:40:08,031
So, tomorrow,

600
00:40:08,532 --> 00:40:09,658
when you leave...

601
00:40:13,703 --> 00:40:16,123
make sure we never see each other again.

602
00:40:59,541 --> 00:41:01,042
No texts,

603
00:41:01,668 --> 00:41:02,961
no calls,

604
00:41:03,962 --> 00:41:05,338
no letters.

605
00:41:07,007 --> 00:41:08,466
Nothing.

606
00:41:10,969 --> 00:41:11,928
Then how?

607
00:41:12,512 --> 00:41:15,307
Telepathy?

608
00:41:15,390 --> 00:41:16,808
Can you do that?

609
00:41:16,892 --> 00:41:18,059
Gem...

610
00:41:20,103 --> 00:41:21,521
There will be a sign.

611
00:41:25,525 --> 00:41:27,819
It's going to mean I'm still alive.

612
00:41:31,239 --> 00:41:34,367
And that I'm following
the plan you made for me.

613
00:41:39,915 --> 00:41:41,917
That sounds difficult.

614
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:43,835
I'm not a fortune‑teller.

615
00:41:46,838 --> 00:41:49,216
You just have to look up at the sky.

616
00:41:50,175 --> 00:41:51,718
Mm.

617
00:41:52,260 --> 00:41:54,012
I promise you.

618
00:41:55,430 --> 00:41:58,516
The sign will be clearer than the moon.

619
00:42:19,579 --> 00:42:21,289
It's beautiful!

620
00:42:22,540 --> 00:42:25,210
- Wow!
- Did you plan this?

621
00:42:26,419 --> 00:42:27,545
Sure.

622
00:42:29,130 --> 00:42:30,257
Do you like it?

623
00:42:33,802 --> 00:42:35,178
It's so pretty.

624
00:42:35,929 --> 00:42:37,264
Perfect timing.

625
00:43:26,396 --> 00:43:27,689
Mm?

626
00:43:27,772 --> 00:43:28,732
Ronnie?

627
00:43:28,815 --> 00:43:30,191
Where's Dad and Issay?

628
00:43:31,192 --> 00:43:32,235
They went out shopping.

629
00:43:32,319 --> 00:43:34,237
They asked me to take care of dinner.

630
00:43:45,665 --> 00:43:46,958
What is it?

631
00:43:47,042 --> 00:43:48,585
I know you went out last night.

632
00:43:48,668 --> 00:43:50,920
I know you have something to do
with the kidnapping.

633
00:44:00,930 --> 00:44:02,599
It's better for you to not know anything.

634
00:44:02,682 --> 00:44:04,684
I want to know about it.
Raya is already affected!

635
00:44:04,768 --> 00:44:06,644
Innocent people are getting involved, Teo!

636
00:44:08,146 --> 00:44:09,647
This isn't like you.

637
00:44:13,777 --> 00:44:15,987
I'm doing this to save people.

638
00:44:16,071 --> 00:44:18,323
So it's better for you
to not know anything.

639
00:44:20,158 --> 00:44:21,910
Gem needs to be freed.

640
00:44:23,745 --> 00:44:26,081
Yana needs to be freed.

641
00:44:27,665 --> 00:44:29,167
Gem is Yana.

642
00:44:29,667 --> 00:44:31,252
The one who toyed with you in Morocco?

643
00:44:52,607 --> 00:44:54,234
What do you really want from me?

644
00:45:06,204 --> 00:45:07,789
I know who you are.

645
00:45:10,792 --> 00:45:12,544
You're the one who beat me up before.

646
00:45:12,627 --> 00:45:14,462
What did I ever do to you, huh?

647
00:45:14,546 --> 00:45:16,506
Did I fail to defend you in court?

648
00:45:16,589 --> 00:45:18,550
Are you a business rival?

649
00:45:22,137 --> 00:45:23,972
Or are you my wife's side piece?

650
00:45:25,056 --> 00:45:26,891
You beat me up
when my wife was in the hospital

651
00:45:26,975 --> 00:45:28,143
after I hit her.

652
00:45:28,685 --> 00:45:30,770
You're probably just exacting
your revenge, right?

653
00:45:30,854 --> 00:45:32,856
Right?

654
00:45:32,939 --> 00:45:33,982
Coward!

655
00:45:35,400 --> 00:45:36,693
Fight me!

656
00:45:36,776 --> 00:45:37,819
Untie me! Let's fight this!

657
00:45:38,820 --> 00:45:39,821
Do it!

658
00:45:50,039 --> 00:45:51,749
No one does that to Ace Verona!

659
00:45:51,833 --> 00:45:53,668
Get back here!

660
00:45:53,751 --> 00:45:55,128
Untie me!

661
00:45:55,211 --> 00:45:56,296
Hey!

662
00:45:56,921 --> 00:45:58,256
Untie me!

663
00:45:58,339 --> 00:46:00,341
We've already traced the location

664
00:46:00,425 --> 00:46:01,718
of your mystery caller.

665
00:46:01,801 --> 00:46:05,138
They're at a junkyard
and impounding area in Bulacan.

666
00:46:05,221 --> 00:46:07,182
And the owner
of the other cell phone number?

667
00:46:07,265 --> 00:46:09,017
A certain Hernando Velez.

668
00:46:09,100 --> 00:46:10,977
But he's not the one calling.

669
00:46:11,060 --> 00:46:13,313
Because that person has been long dead.

670
00:46:13,855 --> 00:46:15,190
Let's raid the place already!

671
00:46:15,273 --> 00:46:16,900
We're wasting precious time!

672
00:46:16,983 --> 00:46:18,526
Ma'am,
the consequences will be worse

673
00:46:18,610 --> 00:46:20,236
if we move hastily.

674
00:46:20,320 --> 00:46:22,405
This operation needs to be
well-planned, ma'am.

675
00:46:23,406 --> 00:46:25,825
Our enemies know what they're doing.

676
00:46:25,909 --> 00:46:27,035
No, they don't.

677
00:46:27,118 --> 00:46:28,536
Because if they were really smart,

678
00:46:28,620 --> 00:46:30,788
they would know
not to make an enemy out of me.

679
00:46:32,540 --> 00:46:33,583
Let's go.

680
00:46:57,649 --> 00:47:01,194
Hello? Get ready.
Any time now, full force!

681
00:47:01,277 --> 00:47:04,739
Ace is at a junkyard near Malasigue!

682
00:47:04,822 --> 00:47:07,283
Get my son out of there now! Quick!

683
00:47:21,714 --> 00:47:23,258
Where should I send the money?

684
00:47:23,341 --> 00:47:24,551
<i>To Cruzada.</i>

685
00:47:24,634 --> 00:47:25,677
What the...

686
00:47:25,760 --> 00:47:27,136
Are you making a fool out of me?

687
00:47:27,220 --> 00:47:28,513
Hurry up.

688
00:47:28,596 --> 00:47:30,848
My son and his wife
had better be there for sure!

689
00:47:30,932 --> 00:47:33,351
And you better not try anything funny.

690
00:47:40,358 --> 00:47:42,777
Chief, I'm on my way to the new location.

691
00:47:42,860 --> 00:47:44,445
Be on the lookout at the junkyard.

692
00:48:03,840 --> 00:48:05,258
Eric.

693
00:48:05,341 --> 00:48:06,926
You wait here.

694
00:48:21,816 --> 00:48:23,026
Come on!

695
00:48:27,363 --> 00:48:28,823
Stay alert!

696
00:49:42,146 --> 00:49:43,314
Hello, Gem?

697
00:49:43,398 --> 00:49:45,233
<i>Some of the men got inside.</i>

698
00:49:45,316 --> 00:49:46,609
Armed.

699
00:49:47,318 --> 00:49:48,945
Seems like they're the Veronas' men.

700
00:49:49,028 --> 00:49:50,029
How's Ace?

701
00:49:50,571 --> 00:49:51,572
Still tied up.

702
00:49:52,281 --> 00:49:54,450
They'll find Ace soon, Teo.

703
00:49:54,534 --> 00:49:56,327
I'll go there. Wait for me.

704
00:49:56,411 --> 00:49:57,829
Okay.

705
00:50:42,331 --> 00:50:43,916
Please help me!

706
00:50:56,179 --> 00:50:58,765
Hey! Please help me!

707
00:50:58,848 --> 00:51:00,725
I'll pay you, no matter how much!

708
00:51:00,808 --> 00:51:02,435
Just get me off this, please!

709
00:51:05,730 --> 00:51:07,231
Help!

710
00:51:07,315 --> 00:51:08,733
Help me, please!

711
00:51:09,817 --> 00:51:11,068
Hey! Anyone there? Get me--

712
00:51:12,945 --> 00:51:14,071
Who's there?

713
00:51:15,156 --> 00:51:16,157
I'm right here!

714
00:51:16,240 --> 00:51:17,074
Help me!

715
00:51:18,868 --> 00:51:20,870
I'm right here! I'm here!

716
00:51:22,663 --> 00:51:23,748
What took you so long?

717
00:51:23,831 --> 00:51:25,374
- Sorry, sir.
- Get this off me, now!

718
00:51:25,458 --> 00:51:26,375
Yes, sir.

719
00:51:26,459 --> 00:51:27,585
Hurry up!

720
00:51:29,796 --> 00:51:30,755
Sir.

721
00:52:07,333 --> 00:52:08,876
- Gem!
- Teo!

722
00:52:08,960 --> 00:52:10,253
I'm over here!

723
00:52:12,505 --> 00:52:13,840
You have to get out of here.

724
00:52:14,674 --> 00:52:15,675
What about you?

725
00:52:15,758 --> 00:52:17,468
I'll take care of myself, all right?

726
00:52:17,552 --> 00:52:20,054
I won't leave
until I know for sure that you're safe.

727
00:52:20,137 --> 00:52:22,598
Gem, this is your only chance.
They're right outside.

728
00:52:22,682 --> 00:52:23,933
- No--
- We don't know

729
00:52:24,016 --> 00:52:25,184
if they've already found Ace.

730
00:52:39,866 --> 00:52:40,867
Psst!

731
00:52:41,576 --> 00:52:42,702
Hurry!

732
00:52:44,453 --> 00:52:46,539
- Here's the money.
- Let me get that.

733
00:52:47,373 --> 00:52:48,416
Hold on.

734
00:52:50,793 --> 00:52:52,295
That's for your family.

735
00:52:52,378 --> 00:52:54,046
Escape from the Veronas.

736
00:52:54,130 --> 00:52:55,965
Go someplace far away, Teo.

737
00:52:56,048 --> 00:52:57,675
That's yours, Yana.

738
00:52:57,758 --> 00:53:00,678
We don't have time to argue.
Just accept it and go!

739
00:53:00,761 --> 00:53:02,179
I'll take care of this.

740
00:53:02,263 --> 00:53:03,556
Let's all meet up.

741
00:53:03,639 --> 00:53:05,308
Sounds good. Give me your phone.

742
00:53:09,729 --> 00:53:11,814
We won't talk anymore, got it?

743
00:53:14,275 --> 00:53:15,693
Take care of yourself.

744
00:53:31,375 --> 00:53:32,460
Chief.

745
00:53:32,960 --> 00:53:35,129
We have just arrived at the junkyard.

746
00:53:36,047 --> 00:53:37,465
Get started.

747
00:54:11,415 --> 00:54:12,667
Hurry! Here.

748
00:54:25,388 --> 00:54:26,639
Hey!

749
00:54:46,742 --> 00:54:47,743
Move! Move!

750
00:54:55,209 --> 00:54:57,795
There he is! Follow him!

751
00:55:26,657 --> 00:55:27,575
It's Ms. Gem!

752
00:55:29,410 --> 00:55:30,411
Ms. Katarina.

753
00:55:30,494 --> 00:55:32,705
What? Were you able to find Ace?

754
00:55:32,788 --> 00:55:33,956
Yes, ma'am.

755
00:55:34,040 --> 00:55:35,666
<i>We also found Ms. Gem.</i>

756
00:55:35,750 --> 00:55:37,793
But there's a problem. She's shot.

757
00:55:37,877 --> 00:55:38,878
Oh, my gosh!

758
00:55:53,642 --> 00:55:55,728
Katarina.

759
00:55:55,811 --> 00:55:57,146
Divino?

760
00:55:57,229 --> 00:55:59,523
Please, make the police stop!

761
00:55:59,607 --> 00:56:00,983
And why?

762
00:56:01,067 --> 00:56:04,570
Just make the police stop!
They're shooting our men!

763
00:56:04,653 --> 00:56:05,946
What are you talking about?

764
00:56:06,030 --> 00:56:07,490
<i>I will explain later!</i>

765
00:56:07,573 --> 00:56:09,366
They've already found Ace!

766
00:56:09,450 --> 00:56:12,661
He could get even more injured, please!

767
00:56:16,040 --> 00:56:17,249
Chief.

768
00:56:17,333 --> 00:56:18,459
Hold your fire.

769
00:56:19,043 --> 00:56:20,544
<i>They're our men.</i>

770
00:56:21,378 --> 00:56:22,922
They already have my son.

771
00:56:25,007 --> 00:56:26,383
Stop firing!

772
00:56:27,218 --> 00:56:29,512
Stop firing! Lower your weapons!

773
00:56:35,351 --> 00:56:36,602
After him!

774
00:56:59,083 --> 00:57:00,000
Where's Ace?

775
00:57:01,168 --> 00:57:02,920
Where the hell is my son?

776
00:57:14,348 --> 00:57:15,266
Shoot!

777
00:58:17,036 --> 00:58:18,370
Hey!

778
00:58:30,007 --> 00:58:31,467
Are you okay?

779
00:58:47,274 --> 00:58:48,359
Damn it!

780
00:58:51,904 --> 00:58:53,447
<i>Ever since Teo arrived here,</i>

781
00:58:53,530 --> 00:58:55,491
<i>problems have been coming</i>
<i>one after another.</i>

782
00:58:55,574 --> 00:58:57,785
<i>And I'm beginning to think</i>
<i>he has something to do with it.</i>

783
00:58:57,868 --> 00:59:00,037
That's why he should stay close,
so we can watch him.

784
00:59:00,120 --> 00:59:01,455
Let's lay low for now.

785
00:59:03,332 --> 00:59:05,584
I can't bear losing you again, Teo.

786
00:59:05,668 --> 00:59:08,754
And I can't go back
to a life without you.

787
00:59:14,677 --> 00:59:17,346
This is dangerous.
You'll only get hurt.

788
00:59:17,429 --> 00:59:18,472
We'll fight this together.

789
00:59:19,223 --> 00:59:20,432
<i>Who's with you?</i>
